Defendant Patsy L Collins in court, in custody with Attorney Jeffrey Jacob De La Rosa.   DA Susan Happ appears for the State of Wisconsin.

--The Court finds that Ms. Collins would have provided contact information for her children, if she had access to her telephone and contacts within.

Statement made by Ms. Collins

The Court sentences Ms. Collins  to  5  years, with an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of  2   years, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of  3  years.  This sentence is to commence FORTHWITH. 

The Court finds that the Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program "Boot Camp".
The Court finds that the Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

The Court orders that for the first 9 months of incarceration Ms. Collins is NOT eligible for CIP or SAP programming, she is eligible thereafter. 

The Court gives  53  days credit for time already served.

The Court orders as conditions of Extended Supervision:
--take all medications that are prescribed as prescribed, in the dosage, amount and at the time as directed
--to comply with any treatment or therapy that DOC deems applicable
--to pay costs of $268 plus $250 DNA surcharge

The Court determines that Ms. Collins has already submitted a DNA sample and therefore is not required with this case.

[MK] case called at 9:40am. 
Attorney Jeffrey J De La Rosa in court.  ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin.
DOC Agent Josh Oddsen is present.
Today's hearing was scheduled in response to Agent Oddsen's 6/29/15 letter informing the Court that Ms. Collins is not cooperating with Pre-Sentence Investigation.
Attorney De La Rosa indicates that he does not have information about why Defendant Patsy Collins does not appear today.  Attorney De La Rosa has concerns that she has not received notice of today's hearing--- Ms. Collins is no longer residing at the Lueder Haus, and he does not know where she is living currently.
Agent Oddsen indicates that Ms. Collins still has not been in contact with him. 
The Court orders issuance of a Bench Warrant- Body Only. 
The Court revokes Bond, indicating that Ms. Collins is not to appear before a magistrate at daily Intake Court; instead Ms. Collins will remain in the Jail so that Agent Oddsen can meet with Ms. Collins in the Jail to conduct his Pre-Sentence Investigation and so that Ms. Collins is available for the Sentencing Hearing.
The Court indicates to Agent Oddsen that he should arrange with the Jail staff to flag this warrant/case so that the Jail staff notifies him as soon as Ms. Collins is taken into custody. 
The Court instructs counsel that, once they are informed that Ms. Collins is in the Jail, they are to contact the JA to reset the sentencing hearing date.  The Court is removing the July 27th Sentencing Hearing date from its calendar.
